India 's Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 50.59 Points
NEW DELHI , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay Stock Exchange ( BSE ) market Friday closed at 3622.22 as against Thursday 's close of 3571.63 , showing a net gain of 50.59 points .
The national index rose by 24.72 points to 1568.83 from previous close of 1544.11 .
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted remarkably up at 348.26 and 147.54 compared with Thursday 's close of 342.95 and 145.40 respectively .
Speculatives strengthened further with improved movements in side stock markets , pushing the sensitive index up by another 51 points on the stock market following sustained buying by local operators as well as fresh purchases by foreign funds and financial institutions .
